2. Information We Collect

We may collect the following categories of information:

A. Account Information

When you create or use an account, we may collect:

Your Firebase user ID
Your email address if you link your account with email/password
Your email verification status
Your sign-in provider, such as email/password or Google Sign-In
B. Profile Information

When you use profile features, we may collect and store:

Your display name
Your player ID / player number
Your country or selected region
Your profile image or avatar
Your public profile status and verification-related flags
C. Gameplay and Competitive Data

To operate the game and competitive systems, we may collect and store:

Match results
Ranking points and ranking history
Wins, losses, streaks, match counts, and similar competitive statistics
Badge progress and profile progression
Online match state data necessary to run live matches and recover disrupted sessions
D. Device, Diagnostics, and Technical Data

We may collect limited technical information, such as:

Crash logs
Error reports
Performance diagnostics
Technical event data necessary to keep the game stable and secure
E. Voice Chat Data

If you use the optional in-game voice feature, we may process:

Voice session participation data
Microphone access during live voice communication
Basic voice session metadata such as room participation identity and profile display information

We do not record or store the content of live voice conversations.

We do not use microphone access unless the voice feature is used.

F. User Content

If you upload a profile picture or provide a display name, that content is processed and stored to display your account properly in the App.

G. Advertising and Analytics Data

If the App shows ads or uses analytics tools, third-party services may collect certain data, such as:

Advertising ID
Approximate data used for ad targeting or measurement
App interaction and usage events
Device and performance-related analytics data
3. Information We Do Not Intentionally Collect

We do not intentionally collect:

Payment card data
Government ID numbers
Precise location/GPS data
Personal contacts, SMS, or call logs
Photo library content other than the specific image you choose to upload as your profile picture

The App does not offer in-app purchases or subscriptions.

4. How We Use Your Information

We use information for the following purposes:

To create and manage your account
To let you sign in, restore your progress, and verify your account
To display your player profile to you and, where applicable, to other players
To operate online matchmaking and live multiplayer matches
To calculate rankings, leaderboard placement, and badge progress
To provide optional voice chat during matches
To show and manage ads, where applicable
To understand app usage and improve gameplay quality, reliability, and user experience
To maintain security, detect abuse, and protect fair play
To diagnose crashes, bugs, and service failures
To comply with legal obligations
5. Legal Basis and Consent

Depending on your location, we may process personal data based on one or more of the following:

Your consent
Performance of a service you requested
Legitimate interests in operating, securing, monetizing, and improving the App
Compliance with legal obligations

When microphone or media-related permissions are requested, they are requested through your device operating system and may be controlled by you in device settings.

6. Microphone Permission

The App may request microphone permission only for the optional in-game voice chat feature.

Microphone access is used only so you can speak in supported live match voice rooms. If you do not grant microphone access, you can still use other parts of the App, but voice communication may not work.

You can revoke microphone permission at any time from your device settings.

7. Profile Pictures and Media Access

If you choose to upload a profile image, the App may access the image you select from your device. We only use the selected image for your player profile and do not access unrelated media content beyond what is required by the operating system picker flow.

8. Public and In-Game Visibility

Some information may be visible to other users inside the App, including:

Your display name
Your avatar
Your ranking or leaderboard presence
Limited profile information needed for online play

This visibility is necessary for gameplay, profile display, online competition, and related social features inside the App.

9. How We Share Information

We do not sell your personal information.

We may share information only in the following situations:

A. Service Providers and Infrastructure Providers

We use trusted third-party services to operate the App, including:

Firebase Authentication
Cloud Firestore
Firebase Storage
Firebase Crashlytics
Firebase Cloud Functions
Google Analytics for Firebase
Google AdMob
LiveKit for voice communication

These providers may process data on our behalf to host infrastructure, authenticate users, store game data, deliver voice features, provide diagnostics, measure usage, and serve ads.

B. Legal Reasons

We may disclose information if required to do so by law, regulation, legal process, or a valid governmental request.

C. Protection and Security

We may disclose information where necessary to protect the rights, safety, property, users, the App, or the public, including fraud prevention, abuse investigation, and service security.

10. Data Storage and Retention

We retain information only for as long as reasonably necessary to:

Provide the App
Maintain your account and progress
Preserve rankings and competitive records
Resolve disputes
Detect abuse or cheating
Comply with legal obligations

If you delete your account, we will delete or anonymize the data associated with your account to the extent technically and legally possible, subject to legitimate retention needs such as security, fraud prevention, or legal compliance.

11. Account Deletion

You may delete your account from inside the App using the in-app account deletion feature.

When you request account deletion, we may delete:

Your authentication account
Your player profile
Your uploaded avatar or profile image
Your cloud-stored account-related data associated with your account

Account deletion is intended to be permanent and may not be reversible.

Some limited technical or security records may be retained where necessary for legal compliance, fraud prevention, platform integrity, or dispute handling.

12. Data Security

We use reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect data, including access controls and backend security rules.

However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

13. Children's Privacy

The App is intended for a mixed audience.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children in violation of applicable law. If you believe a child has provided personal information in violation of applicable law, contact us and we will review and take appropriate action.

If your distribution on Google Play is intended for a mixed audience, you must also ensure your Play Console declarations, SDK behavior, ad settings, and data practices match that audience category and comply with applicable platform rules.

14. International Data Transfers

Your information may be processed on servers located outside your country of residence, depending on the infrastructure of the services we use.

By using the App, you understand that your data may be transferred to and processed in other countries where data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.

15. Your Rights

Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have rights such as:

The right to access your data
The right to request correction of inaccurate data
The right to request deletion of your data
The right to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent
The right to object to certain processing
